GAVIN Hunt has won the race for the plum Kaizer Chiefs head coach job! Hunt has agreed a four-year deal with Amakhosi, replacing Ernst Middendorp, who was sacked earlier this month. He got a nod ahead of Adel Amrouche, who was also strongly considered for the vacant post. Hunt and Chiefs agreed on a range of issues, including the technical stuff, which initially caused a snag. The four-time league winner was at Naturena to sign the deal and is expected to be officially announced by the club on Thursday afternoon. More to follow...